Models like:
GPT-4
Claude
Google Gemini
are not open source. These are proprietary models.

Limitations
Because they are closed-source:
You cannot see the model architecture or weights
You cannot train or modify the model
You must use their API
Your app depends on their pricing and rate limits
you do not have full control.



Open-Source / Open-Weight Models
Examples:
LLaMA
Mistral
Falcon

Advantages
Usually free to download and use
Can be modified or fine-tuned
Can be deployed anywhere
Can run on-premise or in the cloud
You have full control over the model and infrastructure
These models can either be run using an inference API or executed locally.